&gt;         default public ZonedDateTime getZonedDateTime(String zoneString) {
&gt;             return ZonedDateTime.of(getLocalDateTime(), getZoneId(zoneString));
&gt;         }    
&gt;     }
&gt; 
&gt; Like static methods in classes, you specify that a method definition
&gt; in an interface is a static method with the `static` keyword at the
&gt; beginning of the method signature. All method declarations in an
&gt; interface, including static methods, are implicitly `public`, so you
&gt; can omit the `public` modifier.


